description:
&lt;p&gt;Lewisham and Greenwich Trust would like to invite enthusiastic applicants for the post of Consultant Paediatrician with a Special interest in Paediatric Oncology based at Queen Elizabeth Hospital (QEH) Woolwich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a replacement, full time post which attracts 10 PA. This post provides an exciting opportunity to support and develop the well-established Paediatric Oncology Shared Care Unit. The unit comprises a 4 bedded in patient ward and day unit, which provides in-patient care and day case chemotherapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is currently a level 1 unit working closely with Great Ormond Street Hospital, Royal Marsden Hospital and UCL. We have approximately 60 patients currently on treatment and provide a range of care including Late Effects clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post involves working within a team of 15 consultants covering General Paediatrics and Level 2 Neonatal unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. Colin Cunningham, Consultant Paediatrician and Clinical Lead, QEH Site&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 020 8836 5284 (secretary)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;E-mail: Colin.Cunningham@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
